com.nimsoft.nimbus.ci
Class Metric

java.lang.Object
  com.nimsoft.nimbus.ci.Metric

public class Metric
extends Object

Represents a particular metric associated with a Configuration Item.

Metrics are defined in a list maintained by Nimsoft. A metric is a particular measurement that can be collected. For example, Disk Usage is a metric (and "System.Disk", or "1.1", is the associated ConfigurationItem). A metric definition has a pre-defined unit, so, for example, Disk Usage reported in MB is metric 2 and Disk Usage reported in percent is metric 3.

getFullPath

public String getFullPath()
Return the full path (a.k.a. type) of the metric. This includes the path of the metric's configuration item. For example, Disk Usage (in MB) would return "1.1:2".

Returns:
the full metric path.
